main event: Two unidentified circular objects were reported in the sky near Baker, Oregon on October 6, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were photographed and the resulting photographs were submitted as part of a UFO report.
The photographs show a circular object and a dark, undefined object in the night sky.
The report is part of Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program that investigated UFO sightings.
The report includes 9 photographs, although not all of the images are clear or show identifiable objects.
The report is labeled as 'UNCLASSIFIED' and handled by the 'FOREIGN TECHNOLOGY DIVISION, AFSC'.
photographs: yes, 9 photographs were included in the report
